I was asked to take leave by @ IBM (Bank) after that smack-incident. I roamed aimlessly 4 sometime. See, I was younger & I felt so sad. I apologized unconditionally to @ IBM via a descriptive email when working in GAMA in TVM. I wanted My job back in @ IBM & not the Bank or GAMA.

I loved working in @ IBM. I was in @ ATT dept. of @ IBM. @ ATT is the firm where C language was invented. I had a laptop, Amex corporate credit card, plush office environment, so many free high-class trainings & wonderful colleagues. My designation in @ IBM was Technical Team Lead.

Menon-Proposal-Ruination must have been the wicked meddling of Mlecchas & Cigar-Wallas. Wat have Mlecchas gained thru all this? Their own proposal got screwed up. Rite? Then out of desperation, I smacked a junior guy who disrespected Me (Mleccha-Meddling) in @ IBM & I got fired.

Now, how I ended up in mental asylum from @ IBM? Well, I really had a liking for Menon-Girl. I even talked to her cousin who worked in @ IBM that time. The girl used to call Me daily. But, girl's dad called Me one night telling they want to pull out of proposal. I felt dejected.

I was the customer without any hikes or perks in places where I worked like Satyam & @ IBM. What is the use of customer-tag if u are not remunerated enuf? Problem is, the customer-tag of the bank spoils a normal work-life with fellow colleagues. The customer-tag gave Me a halo!

In July 2007, I got fired from @ IBM. I stayed at Rustam Bagh in BGLR during @ IBM times. By that time, Mlecchas were virulent spoiling My life. During My time in @ IBM, Mlecchas ruined My marraiage with a Menon-Girl. A decade later, Mleccha-Proposal got ruined. Effects of Karma!

I did not get deserving hikes in Satyam & @ IBM tho. If u see, whole of My momentary existence on planet Earth was without suitable hikes. All of 15 years of My career were excruciating struggle for survival. One event after another, like a chain reaction. It all started in Sg.

Well, luckily, @ IBM's Policy was to discredit job-histories more than 12 months old. So, I did not have to fabricate much with documentation in @ IBM. But, I had to a lie a lot. I had relieving letter from Kanti, uncle's firm tho. Who gives job to a guy who gets fired regularly?

I managed to get relieving docs from uncle's firm & attended a walk-in interview of @ IBM in TVM in Aug 2006. IBM-Interview was arduous. It took whole day from 8 AM to 10 PM at night. Last Interview-Question was: What is Transaction Manager in Java? I answered it & got the job.
